data.content:
noun
plural -overs
[count, noncount]
the act of delaying the payment of a debt
the act of placing invested money in a new investment of the same kind - see also roll over at 1roll
chiefly US :an accident in which a car, truck, etc., turns over
He was injured in a rollover (accident) on the highway.
chiefly Brit :prize money in a lottery that is not won and so is added to the prize money of the next lottery
